&lt;h1&gt;Visitor Information&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All non-Columbia visitors must meet the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://covid19.columbia.edu/news/fall-2022-update-covid-19-university-guidance"&gt;primary vaccination series mandate&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No registration or tickets required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Exhibit&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;War doesn&amp;rsquo;t knock on your door asking if it can come in. It doesn&amp;rsquo;t warn you what will happen to your life, your family, your community, your town, or your country. It won&amp;rsquo;t tell you what your future will look like. It destroys everything; it takes everything away from you without warning. It gives you one thing in return: the chance to fight back.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ukrainians chose to fight back. Since February 24, 2022, millions of people in Ukraine have resisted Russia&amp;rsquo;s invasion of their country. Some streamed toward new front lines that stretched hundreds of kilometers on sea, land, and air. Some have chosen to dedicate their skills, whatever they might be, to help the country resist. This exhibit is a record of the sacrifice Ukrainians are making and the devastating effect the war has brought to the lives of Ukrainian communities all over the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Artist&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sasha Maslov is a Ukrainian-American portrait photographer and storyteller based in New York City. His work has been exhibited in various photo galleries and art spaces around Europe and the United States. Sasha, a regular contributor to a number of magazines and leading publications in New York and around the globe, is actively pursuing the development of his documentary projects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Teaching in the Morningside eClassroom (for Instructors, Course and Teaching Assistants)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A 60-minute session for Columbia Faculty, Graduate student instructors, course and teaching assistants.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you wondering about the technology available in&amp;nbsp;Morningside classrooms equipped by CUIT to support teaching and learning? Would you like to learn more about the hybrid technology in Morningside classrooms and the support available to you&amp;mdash;both pedagogical and technological&amp;mdash;to enhance the courses you teach?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are new to teaching in Morningside classrooms or seeking a refresher, this joint session offered by Columbia University Information Technology (CUIT) and Columbia Center for Teaching and Learning (CTL) is for you!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Learn about and experience a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://cuit.columbia.edu/classroom-locations" target="_blank"&gt;hybrid classroom&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;environment on Morningside campus, equipped by CUIT to enhance face-to-face instruction as well as support in-person and remote students. We will provide an overview of classroom technology, share pedagogical resources, and leave lots of time for questions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and imagine the possibilities in your classroom!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;This session will be held in a hybrid classroom&amp;nbsp;on&amp;nbsp;Morningside campus. Registered participants can choose to participate in-person or via Zoom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unable to join us for this session?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Learn more about Morningside hybrid classrooms and CUIT eclassroom support&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://cuit.columbia.edu/hybrid-class-checklist" target="_blank"&gt;Hybrid Classrooms: Getting Started Checklist&lt;/a&gt;; Registrar-managed&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://cuit.columbia.edu/classroom-locations" target="_blank"&gt;Hybrid Classroom Locations&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Explore the CTL&amp;rsquo;s portfolio of resources, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/teaching-with-technology/teaching-online/five-tips-hybrid/" target="_blank"&gt;Five Tips for Hybrid/HyFlex Teaching with All Learners in Mind&lt;/a&gt;;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/teaching-with-technology/teaching-online/hyflex/" target="_blank"&gt;Hybrid/HyFlex Teaching and Learning&lt;/a&gt;; and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/teaching-with-technology/teaching-online/flexible-spaces/" target="_blank"&gt;Teaching in Flexible Learning Spaces&lt;/a&gt;; receive customized assistance through&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/teaching-with-technology/teaching-online/get-help/" target="_blank"&gt;office hours&lt;/a&gt;, or by scheduling a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/faculty/offerings/consultations/" target="_blank"&gt;consultation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://cglink.me/2e9/r1669311" target="_blank"&gt;REGISTER HERE: https://cglink.me/2e9/r1669311&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Max Smeets as he discusses his book, &amp;#39;No Shortcuts: Why States Struggle to Develop a Military Cyber-Force&amp;#39;. Through his book, Smeets shows why the challenges faced by governments to develop military cyber capabilities might change over time and explains the limits of capability transfer by states and private actors.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Max Smeets is Senior Researcher at the Center for Security Studies, Zurich; Director of the European Cyber Conflict Research Initiative; and an affiliate at Stanford&amp;rsquo;s Center for International Security and Cooperation.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This event is open to students, faculty,&amp;nbsp;and other invited guests. It will be held in-person (updated: 8/18/2022)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This event is organized by SIPA Tech and Policy, The Saltzman Institute of War and Peace Studies, the Digital and Cyber Group, SIPA International Security Policy Concentration, and SIPA Technology Media and Communication Specialization.&lt;/p&gt;

